  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To verify if the screening opportunistic of Atrial Fibrillation (AF) by means of the
      measurement of the arterial peripheral pulse is more effective than the habitual practice for
      the early detection of AF in 65-year-old who come to Primary care
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
